{"id":30616,"title":"Drug-induced acne and rose pearl: similarities.","abstract":"Drug-induced acne is a common skin condition whose classic symptoms can be similar to a rose pearl, as in the case of a male patient presenting with this condition after excessive use of a cream containing corticosteroids. ","date":"2014-01-29","categories":"Chemically-Induced Disorders","split":"train","url":"http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/24474128","annotations":[{"name":"Acne","weight":0.847047,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Acne"},{"name":"Corticosteroid","weight":0.75769,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Corticosteroid"},{"name":"Cutaneous conditions","weight":0.703787,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cutaneous_conditions"},{"name":"Symptom","weight":0.667165,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Symptom"},{"name":"Skin","weight":0.660386,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Skin"},{"name":"Male","weight":0.379276,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Male"},{"name":"Patient","weight":0.0604488,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Patient"},{"name":"Cream","weight":0.0391252,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cream"},{"name":"Rose","weight":0.0157947,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Rose"},{"name":"Pearl","weight":0.0152478,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Pearl"}]}
